# Layer-boundary exceptions — grandfathered edges that violate the rules in
# scripts/check-layer-boundaries.ts.
#
# This file is intentionally empty on creation (2026-04-24): the current codebase
# has ZERO core -> modules imports, which is the only rule active today. Other
# rules (e.g. src/core/security -> src/core/rendering) activate as Phase 1 of
# the roadmap creates those subfolders. New violations introduced then should
# be fixed in the PR that introduces them; add an entry here only if the fix
# depends on a named later phase.
#
# Format:
#   <source-path> -> <target-path>  # <reason + phase>
#
# Paths are normalized (no extension, no trailing /index). Match the format
# emitted by `npm run check:layers -- list-violations`.
#
# Maintenance rule: when a phase completes, entries for work that phase
# resolved should be removed. If an entry remains, the refactor is incomplete.
